p: The estimation of free energy of binding between potential inhibitors and receptors was performed using a docking experiment. Table 2 and Figure 1 show the docking analysis results between the selected compounds with M pro (3CL pro) and S protein. The docking results showed that some compounds from plants with better binding positions with S protein than nelfinavir were hesperidin, nabiximols, pectolinarin, epigallocatechin gallate, and rhoifolin. Other compounds tended to be better positioned compared to chloroquine and hydroxychloroquine sulfate, except for 6-shogaol. Binding poses to M pro that were better or equivalent to nelfinavir were hesperidin, rhoifolin, and pectolinarin. Some compounds showed better binding poses than chloroquine and hydroxychloroquine on M pro.
